results.title: On the Trail of... The Border Hawk!
The Medicine-Man or: The Parable of the Pitchman's Pitch
[Oh, I ride alone thruout the West...
Revenge of the Enchanters
results.description: Thor and the Warriors Three battle Enrakt the Enchanter; Loki is revealed to be impersonating Odin.

results.title: At Last -- Disclosure!
results.description: Intrigue surrounds Odin in Asgard, while on Earth, Jake Olsen is accused of drug dealing.

results.title: And the Absorbing Man Makes Three!
Hammer Time!
results.description: Thor and Iron Man visit Asgard, which is under reconstruction following the battle with the Dark Gods.  Returning to earth, they battle the Absorbing Man and Titania, and Thor learns that Enrakt the Enchanter has been living inside his hammer.

results.title: The Eighth Day Part 1: Nothing Can Stop the Juggernaut? Don't Tell Thor!
The Eighth Day Part 1
results.description: Thor battles the Juggernaut until the unstoppable mutant is pulled away to join a new band of godlings.

results.title: The Deadly Living Talismans!
results.description: After finishing the battle on Earth, Thor arrives in time to keep the Enchanters from defeating Odin.

results.title: Deviant Life
results.description: The Scarlet Witch helps Thor and Odin defeat the Enchanters, but it's Ceranda's face beneath Enrakt's mask.

results.title: Fast Lane Part 2: Feel the Rush
Thor (1998) #20
results.description: The defeated Enchanters reveal that Enrakt possessed the body of Ceranda.  Later, Thor confronts Jake Olsen, while Mangog steals the Chalice of Ruins for an unseen master.

results.title: Thor (1998) #21
results.description: Thor and Jane travel to Asgard to ask Odin about the puzzle of Jake Olson; Thor finds Asgard in shambles from Mangog's assault; Thor and Mangog clash as Thanos steals the Map of the All-Ending from Odin.

results.title: Fast Lane Part 3: On The Edge
Thor (1998) #22
results.description: Odin observes a possible future where Thanos weilds the ultimate power of death; Thor fails to keep Thanos and Mangog from the Illumination Stone.

results.title: Thor (1998) #23
results.description: Thor and his cosmic allies try and catch up to Thanos and Mangog but are too late to keep him from accosting Tarene, the last piece in the mad Titan's bid for power.

results.title: Fast Lane Part 4: Back on Target
Thor (1998) #24
results.description: Thor and Company track down Thanos and Company before the mad Titan can end all life in the universe; A battle ensues which the heroes lose; The issue ends where the destructive prophecy of issue #22 began.

results.title: Thor (1998) #25
results.description: Thanos gains the ultimate power of death, but Odin sends new enchanted weapons to Thor to help him defeat the mad Titan.

results.title: Winter's Edge
results.description: Following the events of AVENGERS INFINITY, Thor prepares to return to Earth.  Balder must battle Malekith's pawn, Pentigaar, before he can bring a healing potion to the injured Hogun.  Beta-Ray Bill arrives in time to help.
